NOTICE

This software, Safe Device, is a GPU-accelerated face verification system
built with Python. It integrates real-time face detection, 512-dimensional
ArcFace embeddings, blink-based liveness detection, a FastAPI REST backend,
and the FaceGuard desktop access control agent.

Safe Device makes use of the following open-source projects, each governed
by their own respective licenses:

  - InsightFace        — MIT License
                         https://github.com/deepinsight/insightface

  - MTCNN              — MIT License
                         https://github.com/ipazc/mtcnn

  - PyTorch            — BSD License
                         https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch

  - OpenCV             — Apache 2.0 / BSD License
                         https://github.com/opencv/opencv

  - FastAPI            — MIT License
                         https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi

  - ONNX Runtime       — MIT License
                         https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime

  - NumPy              — BSD License
                         https://github.com/numpy/numpy

  - psutil             — BSD License
                         https://github.com/giampaolo/psutil

  - plyer              — MIT License
                         https://github.com/kivy/plyer

The inclusion of these libraries does not imply endorsement by their
respective authors or organizations. All trademarks and registered
trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
